title: s_gundam
body:
A fictional manned military giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in [[Gundam Sentinel]].
 
[b]MSA-0011 S Gundam[/b]

A heavily armored assault [[mobile_suit|MS]] developed by [[Anaheim Electronics]]. Despite its resemblance to the [[ZZ Gundam]], the two were not related, with the S Gundam being more oriented towards use by conventional pilots, being furnished with INCOMs for the quasi-psycommu system and an auxiliary AI, ALICE, to help with controlling the behemoth. The S in its name stands for "Superior".

title: nero_(mobile_suit)
body:
A fictional manned military giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in [[Gundam Sentinel]].
 
[b]MSA-007 Nero[/b]

An Anaheim Electronics mass production version of the [[S Gundam]] with an upper body superstructure based on that of the Lambda Gundam prototype. The result is a high-performance mass production model potentially capable of rivaling higher-class [[mobile suit]]s with proper tuning. 

The design of Nero was also inspired by another of [[Anaheim Electronics]]' mass production mobile suits, the MSA-003 [[nemo_(mobile_suit)|Nemo]].

title: victorious_(kancolle)
body:
[i][[Kantai Collection]][/i] character [[personification|personifying]] "HMS [i]Victorious[/i], pennant number R38":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMS_Victorious_(R38)#Service_with_the_US_Navy], third of four Illustrious-class aircraft carriers of the British Royal Navy. Like all British shipgirls before her, she was fleshed out by [[konishi (koconatu)|Konishi]]. Her voice actress is Yamada Misuzu.

Like some British shipgirls depicted in the game, she is given characteristics such as: [[long_hair|Long]] [[blonde hair]], greenish [[blue eyes]], and a [[medium_breasts|somewhat well-endowed bustline]]. She wears a somehat stylized [[military uniform]] comprising of a greenish [[cropped jacket]] over a [[white shirt|white]] [[dress shirt]] decorated with a [[red flower|red]] [[red_rose|rose]], a [[corset]] attached to an overskirt worn over a [[white_skirt|white]] [[underskirt]], [[black pantyhose]], [[rudder footwear]], [[black gloves]], and a [[pelvic curtain]] resembling an aircraft carrier runway. She also wears a [[tiara]]-like [[hairband]] similar to [[Ark Royal (kancolle)|]]'s. Her [[machinery|rigging]] includes a [[quiver]] to the right of her hip and she wields a [[compound bow]] with a distinct [[flight deck]] motif in her left hand.

Victorious has [[official_alternate_hair_length|also been depicted with]] [[short hair]], mirroring her voice actress's own hairstyle.

Her jacket's hue being close to "robin egg blue" is one of her official links to her brief time as part of the US Navy under the codename "USS [i]Robin[/i]" in 1943. Her seasonal Christmas voice line references this period too, which was unremarkable compared to the rest of her service. Such voice line also references her relationship with [[Saratoga (kancolle)|]], the only active American flight carrier that year to which the historical Victorious provided support. This period of her life service tends to be more fleshed out on fanarts.

title: hornet_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s [[personification]] of the [i]Yorktown[/i]-class [[aircraft carrier]] [[uss_hornet_(cv-8)|USS Hornet, hull number CV-8]], the seventh ship in the US Navy bearing the name.
Character design by [[Konishi (koconatu)]], voiced by [[Fairouz Ai]].

h4. Appearance
Hornet is given characteristics such as: [[long_hair|Long]] flowing [[blonde hair]], [[grey_eyes|grayish blue eyes]], and a [[large_breasts|well-endowed figure]]. She wears a [[white_shirt|white]] [[dress shirt]] with a [[black necktie]] under a [[black jacket|black]] [[bomber jacket]], a [[black belt|black]] [[belt]], a [[black skirt|black]] [[pencil skirt]], [[black pantyhose]], and [[rudder footwear]]. Her damaged CG reveals that her dress shirt [[sleeveless shirt|does not have sleeves]].  To her right is part of her machinery which includes a bridge tower while on her left, she handles an extremely long [[flight deck]]-shaped [[weapon case]] which houses her rifle aircraft "launcher," a modified [[rifle]] topped with several [[Bofors 40 mm gun|Bofors 40-mm gun]]s.

h4. History
The historical [i]Hornet[/i] launched the Doolittle Raid on Tokyo and participated in the [[Battle of Midway]]. She was also involved in the capture and defense of Guadalcanal and the Battle of the Santa Cruz Islands, where she was irreparably damaged by enemy torpedo and dive bombers. She was later abandoned by her crew in the face of an approaching Japanese surface force and later scuttled on October 27, 1942 by destroyers [i][[akigumo (kancolle)|Akigumo]][/i] and [i][[makigumo (kancolle)|Makigumo]][/i], but not before "the crew of the former decided to sketch the wreck":/posts/1559875 as it was too dark to take pictures. The incident is referenced in shipgirl Hornet's sinking line as well as her 4:00 p.m. hourly where she is willing herself to model for the game's resident "manga artist." She also has a relationship with [[shoukaku (kancolle)|Shoukaku]] for the same reason; they were both heavily damaged in the battle as they traded hits but Hornet fell in the end.

Hornet was the last US carrier to be sunk by enemy fire and her service earned her four service stars. Her name was later transferred to "another aircraft carrier, hull number CV-12":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USS_Hornet_(CV-12)], an [i]Essex[/i]-class carrier. Her wreck was located in late January 2019 near the Solomon Islands.

A pentalogy of [[post-apocalypse|post-apocalyptic]] action films set in the barren [[Australia]]n outback with biker gangs, rat rods, psychotic metalhead cults and a young Mel Gibson. Consists of [[Mad Max (1979)|Mad Max]] (1979), [[Mad Max 2: The Road Warrior]] (1981), [[Mad Max Beyond Thunderdome]] (1985),  [[Mad Max: Fury Road]] (2015) and [[Furiosa: A Mad Max Saga]] (2024).

The series has become one of the most influential works of post-apocalyptic fiction. Subsequent post-apocalyptic media often borrow elements from the series, particularly its rat rod vehicle design and the tribalistic elements of each wasteland gang.

title: chinese_bellflower
body:
[b][i]Platycodon[/i][/b], commonly called Chinese bellflower, is a genus of [[flower]]ing plant in the [[bellflower]] family ([i]Campanulaceae[/i]), native to East Asia. The only member of the genus is [i]Platycodon grandiflorus[/i].

Chinese bellflower produces five-petaled, star-shaped flowers that are blue, purple, pink, or white in color. A notable feature is the [[bud]], which swells like a balloon before opening into a star-shaped flower, earning the flower another common name - [b]balloon flower[/b] (which is also a tag, but for literal balloons). The roots of the plant are edible and used in cooking.

Not to be confused with [[balloon flower]], a flower made by tying up a balloon. Also not to be confused with [[flower balloon]], a flower-shaped balloon.

title: long_labia
body:
Long labial lips.

Labia majora are the two outer layers of the vulva, which together with the labia minora form the labia. Labia majora is most often shown covering the labia minora, vaginal opening and urethra in anime/hentai art, as seen in the tag [[cleft of venus]]. Such posts should not be tagged with [[long labia]], unless both variations are shown. 

It can be [[long labia]] even if it's naturally small but it's being stretched.

The medical term is labial hypertrophy. It's a harmless variation from female to female and it is quite common. The main deciding factor is genes, but puberty, chronic hormonal imbalance, and pregnancy can enlarge the labia oftentimes permanently.

title: freight_train
body: A freight train, also called a goods train or cargo train, is a railway [[train]] that is used to carry cargo, as opposed to passengers. Freight trains are made up of one or more [[locomotive]]s which provide propulsion, along with one or more railroad cars (also known as wagons) which carry freight. A wide variety of cargos are carried on trains, but the low friction inherent to rail transport means that freight trains are especially suited to carrying bulk and heavy loads over longer distances. [[Military]] train carrying military equipment also counts as freight train.

title: street
body:
A paved [[road]] in a [[city]] environment, usually designed for both vehicle and pedestrian traffic.

A street is a type of [[road]]. The difference between a road and a street is that [[road]] is for all types of roads, including [[highway]]s and [[dirt road]]s outside of cities, while a street generally refers to a paved road in a city. A street is usually designed to accommodate both vehicle and pedestrian traffic, with intersections, [[traffic light]]s, [[sidewalk]]s, and [[crosswalk]]s. A [[highway]] is usually designed only for high-speed or long distance vehicle traffic and doesn't have these features.

A street can be unpaved dirt, but is most often paved with a hard, durable surface such as asphalt, concrete, cobblestone or brick.

title: the_office
body:
[b]The Office[/b] is an American mockumentary sitcom TV series that depicts the everyday work lives of office employees at the Scranton, Pennsylvania, branch of the fictional Dunder Mifflin Paper Company. It aired on NBC from March 24, 2005, to May 16, 2013, spanning a total of nine seasons. 

Based on the 2001‚Äì2003 BBC series of the same name created by Ricky Gervais and Stephen Merchant, it was adapted for American television by Greg Daniels, a veteran writer for Saturday Night Live, [[King of the Hill]], and [[The Simpsons]]. It was co-produced by Daniels' Deedle-Dee Productions and Reveille Productions (later Shine America), in association with Universal Television. The original executive producers were Daniels, Gervais, Merchant, Howard Klein, and Ben Silverman, with numerous others being promoted in later seasons.

Like its British counterpart, the series was filmed in a single-camera setup without a studio audience or a laugh track to simulate the look of an actual documentary. The series debuted on NBC as a mid-season replacement and aired 201 episodes for its run. The Office originally featured [[Steve Carell]], Rainn Wilson, John Krasinski, Jenna Fischer, and B. J. Novak as the main cast; however, the series experienced numerous changes to its ensemble cast during its run. Notable stars outside the original main cast include Ed Helms, Amy Ryan, Mindy Kaling, Craig Robinson, James Spader, Ellie Kemper, and Catherine Tate.

The Office was met with mixed reviews during its short first season, but the following seasons, particularly Carell's performance, received significant acclaim from television critics as the show's characters, content, structure, and tone diverged considerably from the British version. These seasons were included on several critics' year-end top TV series lists, winning several awards such as a Peabody Award in 2006, two Screen Actors Guild Awards, a Golden Globe Award for Carell's performance, and four Primetime Emmy Awards, including one for Outstanding Comedy Series, in 2006. The eighth season was criticized for a decline in quality. Many saw Carell's departure in season seven as a contributing factor; however, the ninth and final season ended the series with a generally positive response. The series finale, which originally aired on May 16, 2013, was viewed by an estimated 5.7 million viewers and garnered critical acclaim. In 2016, Rolling Stone named The Office one of the 100 greatest television shows of all time.

title: itsuki_shu
body:
[i][[Ensemble Stars!]][/i] character. A third year student and member of [[valkyrie (ensemble stars!)|Valkyrie]]. 

He has [[short hair|short]] [[pink hair]] and [[purple eyes]]. At school, he wears the standard [[yumenosaki school uniform|Yumenosaki uniform]], consisting on [[plaid pants]], a [[blazer]] and a [[frilled neckwear|frilled]] [[necktie]]. For Valkyrie, he wears a [[top hat]], [[frilled jacket]] and a [[long coat]] with [[boots]].

He is an arrogant person who wants everything to go his way. Despite this, he does not like places with many people and is not very good at facing the crowds under lives. As the captain of the handicraft club, he has dexterous and skillful fingers, and made the uniforms of their unit by himself. He's also childhood friends with [[kiryu kuro|Kuro Kiryuu]]. Shu is a "shotacon" and sometimes fawns over cute little boys, like his former unit member [[nito nazuna|Nazuna Nito]] (Shu and Mika consider Nazuna a traitor for leaving Valkyrie, because the latter couldn't stand Shu anymore). [[kagehira mika|Mika Kagehira]] loves and respects him, but Shu is dismissive towards him.

He owns a [[doll]] named [[mademoiselle_(ensemble_stars!)|Mademoiselle]], which he uses to talk through with around people he's not confortable around.

At first he's hostile towards [[anzu (ensemble stars!)|Anzu]] because she and Trickstar got to defeat Fine and [[tenshouin eichi|Eichi Tenshouin]] by extension. He despises Eichi for the Five Oddballs incident, which caused Valkyrie (at the time the strongest unit) to fall from grace.

title: kabru
body:
Kabru is a "tallman*" adventurer in [[dungeon meshi]]. In many regards, he is the polar opposite of [[laios touden|Laios]]; he has a deep contempt for monsters as a result of [spoilers]being orphaned by a dungeon whose monsters spilled out and killed everyone in his homeland[/spoilers]. He was raised by [[milsiril_(dungeon_meshi)|an elf]] who taught him to be an exceptional fighter, however, that training appears to have only been applicable to human* opponents; he and his party lose frequently to monsters in the dungeon that the ostensibly-less-skilled party lead by Laios handle with relative ease.

[tn]* In dungeon meshi, the term "human" applies to many races: halflings, elves, dwarves, gnomes, etc., while the word "tallmen" is used to refer to what most fantasy settings simply call "humans".[/tn]

The majority of his "screentime" thus far has revolved around [spoilers]a time when he and [[Mithrun]] were separated from their respective parties and was forced to care for Mithrun. He consequently learned about the true danger of the dungeon.[/spoilers]

He has [[dark-skinned_male|dark skin]], [[curly_hair|curly]] [[black hair]], and [[green eyes]], and wears a mix of [[leather armor]] and [[chainmail]].

title: vladilena_millize
body:
Vladilena Miliz√©, nicknamed Lena, is a female main character from the light novel series [[86 -EightySix-]]. Lena is one of the Alba, a race characterized by their silver hair (appearing [[light blue hair|light blue]], [[white hair|white]], or [[grey hair|grey]]), and silver eyes (appearing [[grey eyes|grey]]). Lena has [[long hair]] with [[bangs]] that is usually unadorned and loose, with two [[antenna hair|antenna-like ahoge]].  

At the start of the series she is 16 years old, but through a combination of talent and connections has already obtained the commissioned officer rank of Major in the Republic of San Magnolia's military. Lena usually wears a San Magnolia military uniform, which is a blue [[military uniform]] composed of a [[blue jacket|blue]], [[high collar|high-collared]], [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]], [[cropped jacket]] with an [[armband]], a [[white shirt]] with blue and gold trim, a [[blue skirt|blue]] [[high-waist skirt]], a [[white belt|white]] [[o-ring belt|o-ring]] [[belt]] with one strap on one side and two straps on the other, a [[blue headwear|blue]] [[military hat|military]] [[peaked cap]], [[white thighhighs|white]] [[thighhighs]], and [[blue footwear|blue]] [[boots]].  She wears her uniform along with [[white thighhighs]] supported by [[garter straps]] (the author admitted this was due to his own fetish for [[garter belt]]s).

At the beginning of the series she is assigned as the handler of Spearhead Squadron and goes by the call sign Handler One.  After the events of the first cour of the anime/first volume of the light novel, Lena dyes a [[streaked hair|streak]] of her hair [[red hair|red]] and wears a black variant of her uniform, changing the color of her [[black jacket|jacket]], [[black skirt|skirt]], [[black headwear|hat]], [[black thighhighs|thighhighs]], and [[black footwear|boots]], thus including all five colors of the San Magnolia Republic's flag in her appearance. title: date_a_live
body:
A light novel series written by Tachibana Koushi and illustrated by [[Tsunako]].

In the future, spherical so-called "space quakes" have destroyed a great part of Earth's landmass. In response militaries and scientific communities all over the world have worked together to find out the origin of the occurrences, to little effect.

Enter [[Itsuka Shidou]], a young man of above average skill in school but no experience with girls. By accident he stays near the area that was just ravaged by a space quake, only to find [[yatogami tohka|a girl in a warrior dress]] who threatens to kill him. Before he can say much, she disappears. Afterward he learns that she, among others, is a spirit. Spirits come from another world and cause destruction whenever they enter the human world. Shidou is now given a choice to see how the military kills spirits, or take another option: date the spirits, make them fall in love with and surrender their powers to him so they can live among humans without fear of being hunted.

A very dating sim-like adventure begins for Shidou.

title: cocolia_(honkai_impact)
body:
Non-playable character from [[Honkai (series)|]] series.

A member of Anti-Entropy and the owner of an orphanage, she is also known as "Matushka."

[spoiler]Cocolia used to serve the Red Army in Siberia along with Colonel Alexei Zaitsev, [[Bronya Zaychik|Bronya]]'s late father. However, the Honkai broke in Siberia during the 2nd Eruption, killing Alexei in the process, whose dying wish pleads her to use his car key to save his wife and unborn child. Initially not wanting to comply, Cocolia later stumbled upon [[Alexandra Pavlovna Zaychik]], holding her hostage to keep her calm before the two escaped.

Over a decade later, Cocolia captures Bronya who was attempting to assassinate her as a high-profile target, eventually Cocolia adopted Bronya as her daughter along with other known children such as [[Seele Vollerei]], [[Sin Mal]], [[Liliya Olenyeva]], and [[Rozaliya Olenyeva]].[/spoiler]

The [[Benghuai Xueyuan]] iteration of Cocolia, unlike her [[Honkai Impact 3rd|Honkai Impact]] or [[Cocolia Rand|Star Rail]] counterparts, had a biological daughter named Natasha (not to be confused with [[Raven_(honkai_impact)|]] or her [[Natasha (Honkai: Star Rail)|Star Rail]] counterpart) that died. title: battle_of_okinawa
body:
[b]The Battle of Okinawa[/b] (Japanese: Ê≤ñÁ∏ÑÊà¶, Hepburn: [i]Okinawa-sen[/i]), codenamed [b]Operation Iceberg[/b],  was a battle of the Pacific War fought on the island of [[Okinawa]] by the [[United States Army]] and [[United States Marine Corps]] forces against the [[Imperial Japanese Army]].

The initial invasion of Okinawa on 1 April 1945 was the largest amphibious assault in the Pacific Theater of [[World War II]]. The 82-day battle lasted from 1 April until 22 June 1945. After a long campaign of island hopping, the Allies were planning to use Kadena Air Base on the large island of Okinawa as a base for Operation Downfall, the planned invasion of the Japanese home islands, 340 mi (550 km) away.

The battle has been referred to as the "typhoon of steel" in English, of which the Japanese original phrase was "tetsu no b≈çf≈´". The nicknames refer to the ferocity of the fighting, the intensity of Japanese kamikaze attacks and the sheer numbers of Allied ships and armored vehicles that assaulted the island. The battle was the bloodiest in the Pacific, with around 50,000 Allied and 84,166‚Äì117,000 Japanese casualties,  including Okinawans conscripted into the Japanese Army. According to local authorities, at least 149,425 Okinawan people were killed, died by coerced suicide or went missing.

In [[operation_ten-gou|the naval operations surrounding the battle]], both sides lost considerable numbers of [[ship]]s and [[aircraft]], including the [[yamato_(battleship)|Japanese battleship Yamato]]. 

After the American [[victory]] in the battle, which was very costly (50,000 U.S. soldier casualties, includeed 12,500 killed and missing as well as 36,122 wounded), Okinawa provided a fleet anchorage, troop staging areas, and airfields in proximity to Japan for US forces in preparation for "the invasion of the Japanese home islands":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operation_Downfall.

The high number of U.S. casualties in this battle was one of the reasons for their [[Atomic Bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki]] to end [[the Pacific]] war.

title: falklands_war
body:
[b]The Falklands War[/b] ([[spanish_text|Spanish]]: [i]Guerra de Las Malvinas[/i]) was a ten-week undeclared war between [[Argentina]] and the [[United Kingdom]] in 1982 over two British dependent territories in the South Atlantic: the [[Falkland Islands]] and its territorial dependency, South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands. 

The conflict began on 2 April 1982, when Argentina invaded and occupied the Falkland Islands, followed by the invasion of South Georgia the next day. On 5 April, the British government dispatched a naval task force to engage the Argentine Navy and Air Force before making an amphibious assault on the islands. The conflict lasted 74 days and ended with an Argentine surrender on 14 June, returning the islands to British control. In total, 649 Argentine [[military]] personnel, 255 British military personnel, and three Falkland Islanders were killed during the hostilities.

The conflict was a major [[Cold War]] episode in the protracted dispute over the territories' sovereignty. Argentina asserted (and maintains) that the islands are Argentine territory, and the Argentine government thus described its military action as the reclamation of its own territory. The British government regarded the action as an invasion of a territory that had been a Crown colony since 1841. Falkland Islanders, who have inhabited the islands since the early 19th century, are predominantly descendants of British settlers, and strongly favour British sovereignty and culture. Neither state officially declared war, although both governments declared the islands a war zone.

The conflict had a strong effect in both countries and has been the subject of various books, articles, films, and songs. Patriotic sentiment ran high in Argentina, but the unfavourable outcome prompted large protests against the ruling military government, hastening its downfall and the democratisation of the country. In the United Kingdom, the Conservative government, bolstered by the successful outcome, was re-elected with an increased majority the following year. The cultural and political effect of the conflict has been less in the UK than in Argentina, where it has remained a common topic for discussion. 

Diplomatic relations between the United Kingdom and Argentina were restored in 1989 following a meeting in Madrid, at which the two governments issued a joint statement. No change in either country's position regarding the sovereignty of the Falkland Islands was made explicit. In 1994, Argentina adopted a new constitution, which declared the Falkland Islands as part of one of its provinces by law. However, the islands continue to operate as a self-governing British Overseas Territory.

title: 1993_russian_constitutional_crisis
body:
The 1993 Russian constitutional crisis was a major political conflict between President Boris Yeltsin and the Russian parliament.
It began on September 21, 1993, when Yeltsin issued a decree dissolving the parliament, accusing it of obstructing his reforms.
In response, the parliament declared Yeltsin‚Äôs decree invalid, impeached him, and appointed Vice President Alexander Rutskoy as acting president. 

The standoff escalated into armed clashes in Moscow, culminating on October 4, when Yeltsin ordered military forces to storm the White House (the parliament building).
Tanks fired on the building, and troops moved in to suppress the resistance, resulting in significant casualties and the arrest of opposition leaders. 

The crisis ended with Yeltsin‚Äôs victory and the adoption of a new constitution that significantly expanded presidential powers, marking a turning point towards a more centralized and authoritarian government.

title: w_(girls'_frontline)
body:
Scrapped design for what is commonly speculated to have potentially been the sixth member of the [[Anti-Rain (girls' frontline)|AR Team]].

Conceptually, not much is known about her, as she made limited appearances prior to a similar design being implemented in [[Arknights]], in the form of [[W (arknights)|]]. Aside from post #3731497 (shared February 2016 during [[Girls' Frontline]]'s third beta), [[lowlight kirilenko|Hai Mao]] had drawn her with [[M4 SOPMOD II (girls' frontline)|]] on "a signboard":[https://zh.moegirl.org/File:%E6%B5%B7%E7%8C%AB%E7%BB%9C%E5%90%88%E7%89%A9%E7%9A%84W%E7%AD%BE%E7%BB%98.jpg] for a fan of the latter, around 2016 whilst they were selling a new doujin book (to the curiosity of the fan who'd later share the art on Weibo). With the design resemblance, and already designating her with the name W, players have thus decided to refer to this version of her as such too.

Design-wise, just as with Arknights' W, she appears to have white/silver hair along with dark red accents, though more akin to SOPMOD and less like antennae. Though both having bandanas or scarfs, in place of red horns, she wears a headset. Uniquely to her, she appears to have a mole under her left eye, and appears to have a walkie-talkie on her left shoulder. On the signboard, she also has hands like those SOPMOD has. 

Though the association with SOPMOD has brought some speculation as to what her weapon may have been, it is most commonly thought to be the one that Arknights' W is seen with, a Mk18 Mod0 (derived from the SOPMOD accessory system for the [[M4 Carbine]]); otherwise known as the CQBR or CQBW (CQB Weapon), with some proponents of this theory speculating the "W" in her name to derive from the latter, bolstered by the fact that Arknights' W has "CQBW" as her in-game codename. In 2024, Girls' Frontline finally added [[mk.18 (girls' frontline)|a character]] representing the Mk18 Mod0.

Following Hai Mao's departure from MICA Team in 2017, and the formation of HyperGryph, it is probable that Hai Mao recycled the design for Arknights, alongside other elements they contributed that didn't make the cut for Girls' Frontline (such as the proto-Doctor design found with proto-W, or their proposed draft for the early chapters prior to Jano [ÁÉ≠ËøêÂä®] rewriting it, involving an amnesiac Commander awaking in the middle of combat against an abstractly and fantastically strong Sangvis Ferri).

title: thumbnail_surprise
body:
A post which intentionally uses technical tricks to present a full sized image that is deceptively different from its thumbnail.

This tag covers the following types of surprises:

* Animations that build up to a startling climax.
* Animation frame tricks that flip away from the first frame as soon as the full image finishes loading or after a long delay. Danbooru doesn't always use the first frame as the thumbnail, so these tricks may not work.
* Images with optical illusions that exploit digital image resizes and handling of [[transparent background]]s.
* Images with cleverly placed halftone effects that are designed to be completely obfuscated when the image is scaled to thumbnail sizes.

Some tricks exploit a peculiarity of a specific platform, and will only work in certain browsers or on certain websites. In particular, thumbnail surprises from Twitter frequently depend in some way on Twitter's image handling and won't show up correctly on Danbooru.

This tag is for intentional, technical exploits only. For non-technical exploits or artistic accidents, please use the Misleading Thumbnails pool.

h4. See also

* pool #1229 - Misleading Thumbnails
* [[exif thumbnail surprise]]

title: dragon_god_(touhou)
body:
[[Touhou]] character.

The Dragon God is, according to [[Hieda no Akyuu]]'s account in [[Perfect Memento in Strict Sense]], the highest god of [[Gensokyo]]. According to that same account, the dragon looks like a serpent with hands and horns and that is thicker than a great tree that's thousands of years old, and is so long that it can block out the sky. Co-creator of Gensokyo alongside [[Yakumo Yukari]] and the other Youkai Sages, but it has not been seen since it assisted Yukari with constructing the Great Hakurei Barrier.

[[Hakurei Shrine]] is generally attributed to the Dragon God by fans, since it is the nexus point of the Great Hakurei Barrier they helped create, but there is no concrete evidence in canon.

Might be based on the mythological Ry≈´jin, dragon-god of the ocean and storms, though more canonical information points towards Tenryuu, the celestial dragon of the [[Big Dipper]], which would also give it a connection to [[Matara Okina]].

body: Beetlejuice Beetlejuice is a 2024 American dark fantasy comedy horror film directed by Tim Burton from a screenplay by Alfred Gough and Miles Millar. A sequel to [[Beetlejuice]] (1988) and the second film of the Beetlejuice franchise, the film stars [[Michael Keaton]], Winona Ryder, and Catherine O'Hara reprising their roles alongside new cast members Justin Theroux, Monica Bellucci, Jenna Ortega, and [[Willem Dafoe]]. title: audi_r8
body:
A [[sports car|supercar]] produced by [[Audi]], first released in 2006. Audi has announced that 2023 would be the final model year for the R8, with no current word on a successor.

The R8 has several appearances in popular media, most notably as [[Tony Stark]]/[[Iron Man]]'s personal car throughout the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] films, and one was used as the vehicle mode for [[Sideways (transformers)|]] in [i][[Transformers: Revenge of the Fallen]][/i]. 
The [b]Audi Le Mans Quattro[/b], the concept car that the R8 is based on, also appeared in [i][[Need for Speed: Carbon]][/i] as the car of Darius, the main antagonist.

title: need_for_speed:_carbon
body:
A 2006 entry in the [[Need for Speed]] franchise, and direct sequel to [[Need for Speed: most wanted (2005)|Most Wanted]]. Despite being a sequel to MW, Carbon featured different progression, mostly focused around winning races to capture parts of the city. The most notable feature of the game are the Canyon Battles, 1v1 boss races on narrow, winding roads inspired by Japanese touge racing.

While the game's cover depicts a Canyon Battle between a [[Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution]] and a [[Dodge Challenger (3rd generation)|3rd gen]] [[Dodge Challenger]], the most well known car from this installment is the [[Audi R8]] (listed under its concept name of [b]Audi Le Mans Quattro[/b]) driven by the main antagonist Darius.

title: need_for_speed:_underground_2
body:
A 2004 installment in the [[Need for Speed]] franchise, and direct sequel to [[Need for Speed: Underground]]. Underground 2 is particularly notable for being the first NFS game to feature a fully open world and free roam, features that would become mainstays in the franchise.

The game's cover car is a custom green [[Nissan 350Z]] belonging to Rachel Teller, the player's friend. It also returns in many later installments.

title: need_for_speed:_underground

It's construction is that of a long wrap-around [[robe]] with a y-shaped collar and a [[sash]] around the waist or hips. A type of [[multicolored hair]] where the hair at the top of the head (the [i]roots[/i]) is a different color from the rest. This is typically visible where the hair parts on the head.

This is traditionally a result of neglecting one's dyed hair, letting the natural hair color grow back in. Nowadays it may also be an intentional hairstyle, with people deliberately dying their hair this way. Most often, roots are seen with [[blonde hair]] and appear as dark, natural colors like [[brown hair|brown]] or [[black hair|black]].

Notable characters with this style of hair include [[Miyamori Aoi]], [[Memcho]], [[Sawatari Akane (chainsaw man)|]], and [[Kozume Kenma]].

title: master_spark
body:
[b]Love Sign: Master Spark[/b]

[[Kirisame Marisa]]'s most commonly used and powerful spellcard attack. It appears in almost all of the [[Touhou]] series games (PoFV, MoF and the PC-98 games excluded.)

Despite being originally created and used by [[Kazami Yuuka]],  Marisa (after "borrowing" it) has made it a trademark spellcard of hers, to the point where one of her theme songs is titled "Love-Colored Master Spark".

[i]This is how Marisa uses it:[/i]
* Concentrate your mind 
* Mutter the spell to the Mini-Hakkero tenderly 
* Aim at someone you don't like 
* Now unleash your annihilation of love!

There's also Marisa's "Last Word" spellcard, known as "Magicannon: Final Spark", "Dual Spark", used by Yuka, which is two Master Sparks fired at once (one being fired by a projected doppelganger), and [[Mima (touhou)|]]'s fan-made Twilight Spark, which is usually a dark violet in color and extremely wide. An even stronger version exists in fanworks as "Magicannon: Final Master Spark", but is rarely seen.

h4. See also
[[Dark Spark (touhou)|]]

title: lily_of_the_valley
body:
[i][b]Convallaria[/b][/i] is a poisonous woodland flowering plant in the family [i]Asparagaceae[/i], native to cool temperate climates in North America, Europe, and Asia. Its Japanese name is Èà¥Ëò≠ / „Çπ„Ç∫„É©„É≥ ([i]suzuran[/i]) and its Chinese name is Èà¥Ëò≠ / ÈìÉÂÖ∞ ([i]Linglan[/i]).

The [[flower]]s come in clusters, dangling from curved, alternating offshoots from a main stem (aka raceme) and are bell-shaped and (usually) [[white flower|white]]. All parts of the plant are poisonous, including its red berries.

Not to be confused with [[snowbell (flower)|]]s, as they bear a strong resemblance to lily of the valley. Visual points to note: [i]Snowbells[/i] have a green or yellow spot on the tip of each petal; each flower-bearing stem (called a pedicel) ends in a "bulb" (receptacle) to which a flower is attached. A good visual example is post #2894988 with snowbells on the left and lilies of the valley on the right. Also, not to be confused with [[bellflower]] whose flowers typically have a longer, less rounded bell shape.

Often associated with the characters [[Medicine Melancholy]] and [[Suzuran (arknights)|]].
